blocks.text: This is our lecture12 Framer X project exercise. In order to complete it follow the next instructions:
- Clone the repository to your local drive.
- Open it with WebStorm (preferred), VCS or any other Integrated Development Environment.
- Create a branch with a branch name following this given pattern: yourSurname_TwoWordsDescribingYourProject and check out this branch
(for example, my branch name will be farssac_ExerciseDescription
- Create a Frame under this “explanations Frame”. This Frame will be your exercise and contribution to the group project.
- As you progress with your design, commit changes from within the Integrated Development Environment. (make sure that you commit to your branch name !!)
- Push your commits now and then to the central repository.
- More instructions will be given latter.
- You make commits to the master branch (I will put your name in the black list )
- Others (I will add them here as soon as you manage to surprise me, don’t do that on purpose please :)
